HEADWORD: Pinacone
<hw>Pin"a*cone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Gr. <?/, <?/,
a tablet. So called because it unites with water so as to form
tablet-shaped crystals.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white
crystalline substance related to the glycols, and made from acetone;
hence, by extension, any one of a series of substances of which pinacone
proper is the type.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pinakone</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinacotheca</ent>⟦br⟧
